              "content": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "data": "The `peer` auth method means it checks your OS username matches the PostgreSQL username. You're not logged in as `postgres` OS user.\n\n**Quick fix — use sudo to become the postgres user:**\n\n```bash\nsudo -u postgres psql\n```\n\nThis bypasses the password entirely since peer auth trusts the OS user identity.\n\n**If you need to switch to password auth**, edit `pg_hba.conf`:\n\n```bash\n# Find it\nsudo -u postgres psql -c \"SHOW hba_file;\"\n\n# Change the line:\n# local   all   postgres   peer\n# to:\n# local   all   postgres   md5\n\n# Then restart\nsudo systemctl restart postgresql\n```\n\nBut `sudo -u postgres psql` is the simplest way in."
                }
              ],
