              "content": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "data": "Good, you're in. Now you can set a password for the `postgres` user:\n\n```bash\nsudo -u postgres psql -c \"ALTER USER postgres PASSWORD 'your_desired_password';\"\n```\n\nThen if you want to connect with `psql -U postgres` directly (without sudo), change peer to md5:\n\n```bash\nsudo nano /etc/postgresql/14/main/pg_hba.conf\n```\n\nFind the line:\n```\nlocal   all   postgres   peer\n```\n\nChange to:\n```\nlocal   all   postgres   md5\n```\n\nThen restart:\n```bash\nsudo systemctl restart postgresql\n```\n\nAfter that, `psql -U postgres` will prompt for the password you just set."
                }
